tIPv6FilterParamsAction.description: The action to take for packets that match this filter entry. The value default(3) specifies this entry to inherit the behavior defined as the default for the filter. The value nat(5) is not supported.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNH.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNH
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNH.description: The ipv6-address of the nexthop to which the packet should be forwarded if it hits this filter entry. The action of this entry should be 'forward' in such a case.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect.description: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHIndirect specifies if the nexthop is directly or indirectly reachable.

tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCP.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCP
tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCP.description: The DSCP value that should be remarked in case a packet hits this filter entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask
tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask.description: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDSCPMask specifies the care bits while remarking with the DSCP value.

tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p.name: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p
tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p.description: tIPv6FilterParamsRemarkDot1p specifies the Dot1p value that needs to be remarked on the packet if it hits this filter entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr
tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr.description: IPv6 address to match the source-ip of the packet.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpMask.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpMask
tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpMask.description: The IPv6 Mask value for this policy IPv6 Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the IPv6 to match the tIPv6FilterParamsSourceIpAddr.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr
tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.description: IPv6 address to match the destination-ip of the packet.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpMask.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpMask
tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpMask.description: The IPv6 Mask value for this policy IPv6 Filter entry. The mask is ANDed with the IPv6 to match the tIPv6FilterParamsDestinationIpAddr.

tIPv6FilterParamsNextHeader.name: tIPv6FilterParamsNextHeader
tIPv6FilterParamsNextHeader.description: IPv6 next header to match. set to -1 to disable matching IPv6 next header. If the next header is changed the next header specific parameters are reset. For instance if next header is changed from TCP to UDP, then the objects tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn and tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck will be turned off. Because the match criteria only pertains to the last next-header, the following values are not accepted: 0, 43, 44, 50, 51, and 60.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue1.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue1
tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue1.description: TCP/UDP port value1. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue2.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue2
tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortValue2.description: TCP/UDP port value2. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.name: tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator
tIPv6FilterParamsSourcePortOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue1 and tIPFilterParamsSourcePortValue2 are to be used.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue1.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue1
tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue1.description: TCP/UDP port value1. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue2.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue2
tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortValue2.description: TCP/UDP port value2. The value of this object is used as per the description for tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.

tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator
tIPv6FilterParamsDestPortOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue1 and tIPFilterParamsDestPortValue2 are to be used.

tIPv6FilterParamsDSCP.name: tIPv6FilterParamsDSCP
tIPv6FilterParamsDSCP.description: DSCP to be matched on the packet.

tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn
tIPv6FilterParamsTcpSyn.description: If Enabled, matches a TCP Syn as per value of the object.

tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck
tIPv6FilterParamsTcpAck.description: If Enabled, matches a TCP Ack as per value of the object.

tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode
tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode.description: Icmp code to be matched. tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode complements the object tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType. Both of them need to be set to actually enable ICMP matching. The value -1 means Icmp code matching is not enabled.

tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType
tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType.description: Icmp type to be matched. tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpType complements the object tIPv6FilterParamsIcmpCode. Both of them need to be set to actually enable ICMP matching. The value -1 means Icmp type matching is not enabled.

tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdSample.name: tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdSample
tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdSample.description: When tIPFilterParamsCflowdSample has a value of 'true', Cflowd sampling and analysis is performed on those packet streams where this filter has been applied. Only packets matching this IPv6 filter entry are subjected to Cflowd sampling and analysis. A Cflowd profile controls the sampling and analysis of data flows through the router.

tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample.name: tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample
tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample.description: When tIPv6FilterParamsCflowdIfSample has a value of 'true', Cflowd sampling and analysis is performed on those packet streams where this filter has been applied. Only packets matching this IPv6 filter entry are subjected to Cflowd sampling and analysis. A Cflowd profile controls the sampling and analysis of data flows through the router.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHInterface.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHInterface
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardNHInterface.description: The interface name for the nexthop to which the packet should be forwarded if it hits this filter entry. The action of this entry should be 'forward' in such a case.

tIPv6FilterParamsIngressHitCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIngressHitCount
tIPv6FilterParamsIngressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an ingress packet matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsEgressHitCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsEgressHitCount
tIPv6FilterParamsEgressHitCount.description: This object indicates the number of times an egress packet matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated.name: tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated
tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated.description: tIPv6FilterParamsLogInstantiated indicates if the filter log for this filter entry has been instantiated or not.

tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy.name: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy
tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy.description: tIPv6FilterParamsForwardRedPlcy specifies the redirect policy to be used to determine the nexthop.

tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest.name: tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest
tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest.description: tIPv6FilterParamsActiveDest indicates the IPv6 address of the active destination for this IPv6 filter. A value of 0 indicates that there is currently no active destination.

tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName
tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName.description: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName specifies the tmnxTimeRangeEntry to be associated with this filter entry. A value for this object can only be specified during row creation, and cannot be altered lateron. Also, a value is accepted only if the tmnxTimeRangeEntry is defined in the TIMETRA-SCHEDULER-MIB::tmnxTimeRangeTable.tTimeRangeName.

tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState.name: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState
tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState.description: tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeState indicates whether or not the entry is currently in effect. - timeRangeNotApplic: no time range is applicable for this entry. - timeRangeNotActive: A time range is defined in tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName, but is not active at this moment. Consequently the filter entry is not installed. - timeRangeActive. A time range is defined in tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated successfully. - timeRangeActiveDownloadFailed: A time range is defined in tIPv6FilterParamsTimeRangeName, and is activated, but the corresponding filter entry could not be installed due to resource problems.

tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount
tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount.description: The value of tIPv6FilterParamsIngrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all ingress packets that matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.name: tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount
tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount.description: This tIPv6FilterParamsEgrHitByteCount indicates the number of bytes of all egress packets that matched this entry.

tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSvcId.name: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSvcId
tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSvcId.description: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSvcId indicates the service id of the destination for this filter entry. The value 0 indicates that there is no active SAP or SDP destination.

tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapPortId.name: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapPortId
tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapPortId.description: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapPortId specifies the sap port id of the destination for this filter entry. The value 0 indicates that there is no SAP destination defined. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the value of the tIPv6FilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the object tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSdpBind is '0'.

tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal.name: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal
tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal.description: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal specifies the sap port encap value of the destination SAP for this filter entry. A value different from 0 can only be specified if the value of the tIPv6FilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the object tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSdpBind has value '0'. The value 0 indicates that either 1) the sap encapsulation value is not specified when tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapPortId and tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSvcId have valid values; or 2) that there is no SAP destination.

tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSdpBind.name: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSdpBind
tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSdpBind.description: tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSdpBind specifies the sdp bind id of the destination for this filter entry. The value '0' indicates that there is currently no SDP binding defined. A value different from '0' can only be specified if the value of the tIPv6FilterParamsAction object of this entry is 'forward'. In addition a non-zero value can only be given if the objects tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapPortId and tIPv6FilterParamsFwdSapEncapVal have value 0.

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterType.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterType
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterType.description: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterType specifies the type of the filter referred to by tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterId. Inserted entries can only occur in 'fltrtypeselIp' and 'fltrtypeselIpv6'

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterId.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterId
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterId.description: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFilterId specifies for which filter the inserted entries must be grouped.

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesApplication.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesApplication
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesApplication.description: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesApplication specifies for which application the the inserted entries must be grouped.

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesLocation.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesLocation
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesLocation.description: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesLocation specifies at what location the inserted entries must be grouped.

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesResult.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesResult
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesResult.description: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesResult indicates the success or failure of the last requested grouping request on inserted entries.

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFeedback.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFeedback
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFeedback.description: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFeedback may indicate additional info on the last inserted filter entries grouping action performed.

tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesExecute.name: tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesExecute
tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesExecute.description: Setting the object tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesExecute to 'true' will cause the system to attempt to execute te grouping command as specified by the other MIB objects in the tFilterGroupInsertedEntries mibgroup. When read the value will always indicate 'false'. The result of the command can be found in tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesResult and tFltrGrpInsrtdEntriesFeedback

tDhcpFilterTableLastChanged.name: tDhcpFilterTableLastChanged
tDhcpFilterTableLastChanged.description: The value of tDhcpFilterTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tDhcpFilterTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tDhcpFilterTable.name: tDhcpFilterTable
tDhcpFilterTable.description: Contains a list of all DHCP filters configured on this system.

tDhcpFilterEntry.name: tDhcpFilterEntry
tDhcpFilterEntry.description: Information about a particular DHCP filter. Entries are created/deleted by user. Entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tDhcpFilterId.name: tDhcpFilterId
tDhcpFilterId.description: Uniquely identifies a mac filter as configures on this system.

tDhcpFilterRowStatus.name: tDhcpFilterRowStatus
tDhcpFilterRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tDhcpFilterTable.

tDhcpFilterLastChanged.name: tDhcpFilterLastChanged
tDhcpFilterLastChanged.description: The value of tDhcpFilterLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tDhcpFilterTable.

tDhcpFilterParamsTblLastChanged.name: tDhcpFilterParamsTblLastChanged
tDhcpFilterParamsTblLastChanged.description: The value of tDhcpFilterParamsTblLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tDhcpFilterParamsTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tDhcpFilterParamsTable.name: tDhcpFilterParamsTable
tDhcpFilterParamsTable.description: A table of all DHCP filter match entries for all DHCP filters.

tDhcpFilterParamsEntry.name: tDhcpFilterParamsEntry
tDhcpFilterParamsEntry.description: Information about a particular DHCP filter entry. Every DHCP filter can have zero or more DHCP filter match entries. A filter entry with no match criteria set will match every packet, and the entry action will be taken. Entries are created/deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

tDhcpFilterParamsId.name: tDhcpFilterParamsId
tDhcpFilterParamsId.description: This is the secondary index for the entry. Every DHCP filter can have multiple entries, therefore every DHCP filter entry is identified by the tDhcpFilterId and tDhcpFilterParamsId.

tDhcpFilterParamsRowStatus.name: tDhcpFilterParamsRowStatus
tDhcpFilterParamsRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the tDhcpFilterParamsTable.

tDhcpFilterParamsLastChanged.name: tDhcpFilterParamsLastChanged
tDhcpFilterParamsLastChanged.description: The value of tDhcpFilterParamsLastChanged indicates the timestamp of last change to this row in tDhcpFilterParamsTable.

tDhcpFilterParamsOptionNumber.name: tDhcpFilterParamsOptionNumber
tDhcpFilterParamsOptionNumber.description: The value of tDhcpFilterParamsOptionNumber specifies the number of the DHCP option to filter on.

tDhcpFilterParamsOptionMatch.name: tDhcpFilterParamsOptionMatch
tDhcpFilterParamsOptionMatch.description: The value of tDhcpFilterParamsOptionMatch specifies the criteria that the DHCP option must match to trigger this filter entry. The value present(1) specifies that the DHCP option must be present, the value absent(2) specifies that the DHCP option must be absent. In these cases tDhcpFilterParamsOptionValue will be reset to an empty string. A value string(3), string-exact(4), string-invert(5), string-exact-invert(6), hex(7), hex-exact(8), hex-invert(9) or hex-exact-invert(10) requires an octet string to be present in tDhcpFilterParamsOptionValue to match against.

tDhcpFilterParamsAction.name: tDhcpFilterParamsAction
tDhcpFilterParamsAction.description: The action to take for DHCP host creation requests that match this filter entry. The value none(1) specifies normal host creation behaviour, the value bypass-host-creation(2) specifies to bypass host creation, the value drop(3) specifies to drop the DHCP message.

tDhcpFilterParamsOptionValue.name: tDhcpFilterParamsOptionValue
tDhcpFilterParamsOptionValue.description: The value of the object tDhcpFilterParamsOptionValue specifies the matching pattern for the filtered DHCP option. This object is mandatory at creation time. A zero length value is only allowed when the value of tDhcpFilterParamsOptionMatch is present(1) or absent(2).

tMacFilterNameTableLastChgd.name: tMacFilterNameTableLastChgd
tMacFilterNameTableLastChgd.description: The value of tMacFilterNameTableLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tMacFilterNameTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tMacFilterNameTable.name: tMacFilterNameTable
tMacFilterNameTable.description: A table that contains MAC filter name information. Entries are created automatically by the system when tMacFilterName object is set for the MAC filter.

tMacFilterNameEntry.name: tMacFilterNameEntry
tMacFilterNameEntry.description: Basic information about a specific MAC filter name.

tMacFilterNameId.name: tMacFilterNameId
tMacFilterNameId.description: The value of the object tMacFilterNameId specifies the filter name associated with this MAC filter.

tMacFilterNameRowStatus.name: tMacFilterNameRowStatus
tMacFilterNameRowStatus.description: This value of the object tMacFilterNameRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tMacFilterNameLastChanged.name: tMacFilterNameLastChanged
tMacFilterNameLastChanged.description: The value of tMacFilterNameLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tIpFilterNameTableLastChgd.name: tIpFilterNameTableLastChgd
tIpFilterNameTableLastChgd.description: The value of tIpFilterNameTableLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tIpFilterNameTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tIpFilterNameTable.name: tIpFilterNameTable
tIpFilterNameTable.description: A table that contains IP filter name information. Entries are created automatically by the system when tIpFilterName object is set for the IP filter.

tIpFilterNameEntry.name: tIpFilterNameEntry
tIpFilterNameEntry.description: Basic information about a specific IP filter name.

tIpFilterNameId.name: tIpFilterNameId
tIpFilterNameId.description: The value of the object tIpFilterNameId specifies the filter name associated with this IP filter.

tIpFilterNameRowStatus.name: tIpFilterNameRowStatus
tIpFilterNameRowStatus.description: This value of the object tIpFilterNameRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tIpFilterNameLastChanged.name: tIpFilterNameLastChanged
tIpFilterNameLastChanged.description: The value of tIpFilterNameLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tIpv6FilterNameTableLastChgd.name: tIpv6FilterNameTableLastChgd
tIpv6FilterNameTableLastChgd.description: The value of tIpv6FilterNameTableLastChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tIpv6FilterNameTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tIpv6FilterNameTable.name: tIpv6FilterNameTable
tIpv6FilterNameTable.description: A table that contains IPv6 filter name information. Entries are created automatically by the system when tIpv6FilterName object is set for the IPv6 filter.

tIpv6FilterNameEntry.name: tIpv6FilterNameEntry
tIpv6FilterNameEntry.description: Basic information about a specific IPv6 filter name.

tIpv6FilterNameId.name: tIpv6FilterNameId
tIpv6FilterNameId.description: The value of the object tIpv6FilterNameId specifies the filter name associated with this IPv6 filter.

tIpv6FilterNameRowStatus.name: tIpv6FilterNameRowStatus
tIpv6FilterNameRowStatus.description: This value of the object tIpv6FilterNameRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tIpv6FilterNameLastChanged.name: tIpv6FilterNameLastChanged
tIpv6FilterNameLastChanged.description: The value of tIpv6FilterNameLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiReservedBlockTableLastChanged.name: tLiReservedBlockTableLastChanged
tLiReservedBlockTableLastChanged.description: The object tLiReservedBlockTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tLiReservedBlockTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiReservedBlockTable.name: tLiReservedBlockTable
tLiReservedBlockTable.description: The table tLiReservedBlockTable describes LI reserved blocks. In this release this table can have at most one entry.

tLiReservedBlockEntry.name: tLiReservedBlockEntry
tLiReservedBlockEntry.description: Information about an LI reserved block. This block can be associated with one or more filters to reserve a number of entries in those filters for LI.

tLiReservedBlockName.name: tLiReservedBlockName
tLiReservedBlockName.description: The object tLiReservedBlockName uniquely identifies an LI reserved block.

tLiReservedBlockRowStatus.name: tLiReservedBlockRowStatus
tLiReservedBlockRowStatus.description: The object tLiReservedBlockRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tLiReservedBlockLastChanged.name: tLiReservedBlockLastChanged
tLiReservedBlockLastChanged.description: The object tLiReservedBlockLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiReservedBlockDescription.name: tLiReservedBlockDescription
tLiReservedBlockDescription.description: The object tLiReservedBlockDescription specifies a description for this LI reserved block.

tLiReservedBlockStart.name: tLiReservedBlockStart
tLiReservedBlockStart.description: The object tLiReservedBlockStart specifies the starting entry of the LI reserved block. If set to '0' no block is reserved. In this case the value of the object tLiReservedBlockSize will be set to '0' by the system.

tLiReservedBlockSize.name: tLiReservedBlockSize
tLiReservedBlockSize.description: The object tLiReservedBlockSize specifies the size of the LI reserved block. If set to '0' no block is reserved. In this case the value of the object tLiReservedBlockStart will be set to '0' by the system.

tLiReservedBlockFltrTableLastChg.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrTableLastChg
tLiReservedBlockFltrTableLastChg.description: The value of tLiReservedBlockFltrTableLastChg indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tLiReservedBlockFltrTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiReservedBlockFltrTable.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrTable
tLiReservedBlockFltrTable.description: The table tLiReservedBlockFltrTable contains associations between normal filters and LI block reservations.

tLiReservedBlockFltrEntry.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrEntry
tLiReservedBlockFltrEntry.description: An association of a normal filter with an LI block reservation. In this release, only MAC filters are supported.

tLiReservedBlockFltrType.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrType
tLiReservedBlockFltrType.description: The object tLiReservedBlockFltrType specifies the type of filter this LI block reservation applies to. In this release only MAC filters are supported.

tLiReservedBlockFltrIdStart.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrIdStart
tLiReservedBlockFltrIdStart.description: The object tLiReservedBlockFltrIdStart specifies the ID of the first filter to apply an LI block reservation. In this release, tLiReservedBlockFltrIdStart must be equal to tLiReservedBlockFltrIdEnd.

tLiReservedBlockFltrIdEnd.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrIdEnd
tLiReservedBlockFltrIdEnd.description: The object tLiReservedBlockFltrIdEnd specifies the ID of the last filter to apply an LI block reservation. In this release, tLiReservedBlockFltrIdEnd must be equal to tLiReservedBlockFltrIdStart.

tLiReservedBlockFltrRowStatus.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrRowStatus
tLiReservedBlockFltrRowStatus.description: The object tLiReservedBlockFltrRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tLiReservedBlockFltrLastChanged.name: tLiReservedBlockFltrLastChanged
tLiReservedBlockFltrLastChanged.description: The object tLiReservedBlockFltrLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiFilterTableLastChanged.name: tLiFilterTableLastChanged
tLiFilterTableLastChanged.description: The object tLiFilterTableLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tLiFilterTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiFilterTable.name: tLiFilterTable
tLiFilterTable.description: The table tLiFilterTable contains information about all LI MAC filters.

tLiFilterType.name: tLiFilterType
tLiFilterType.description: The object tLiFilterType specifies the type of this LI filter. In this release only MAC filters are supported.

tLiFilterName.name: tLiFilterName
tLiFilterName.description: The object tLiFilterName indicates the unique name of this LI MAC Filter.

tLiFilterRowStatus.name: tLiFilterRowStatus
tLiFilterRowStatus.description: The object tLiFilterRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tLiFilterLastChanged.name: tLiFilterLastChanged
tLiFilterLastChanged.description: The object tLiFilterLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiFilterDescription.name: tLiFilterDescription
tLiFilterDescription.description: The object tLiFilterDescription specifies a description for this LI MAC filter.

tLiFilterAssociationTableLastChg.name: tLiFilterAssociationTableLastChg
tLiFilterAssociationTableLastChg.description: The object tLiFilterAssociationTableLastChg indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tLiFilterTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiFilterAssociationTable.name: tLiFilterAssociationTable
tLiFilterAssociationTable.description: The table tLiFilterAssociationTable contains information about the associations between LI filters and normal filters.

tLiFilterAssociationEntry.name: tLiFilterAssociationEntry
tLiFilterAssociationEntry.description: An association between an LI filter and a normal filter.

tLiFilterAssociationFltrId.name: tLiFilterAssociationFltrId
tLiFilterAssociationFltrId.description: The object tLiFilterAssociationFltrId indicates the id of the normal filter in the association described by this entry.

tLiFilterAssociationRowStatus.name: tLiFilterAssociationRowStatus
tLiFilterAssociationRowStatus.description: The object tLiFilterAssociationRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tLiFilterAssociationLastChg.name: tLiFilterAssociationLastChg
tLiFilterAssociationLastChg.description: The object tLiFilterAssociationLastChg indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiMacFilterParamsTableLastChg.name: tLiMacFilterParamsTableLastChg
tLiMacFilterParamsTableLastChg.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsTableLastChg indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tLiMacFilterParamsTable. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiMacFilterParamsTable.name: tLiMacFilterParamsTable
tLiMacFilterParamsTable.description: The table tLiMacFilterParamsTable contains all LI MAC filter match entries for all LI MAC filters.

tLiMacFilterParamsEntry.name: tLiMacFilterParamsEntry
tLiMacFilterParamsEntry.description: An LI MAC filter match entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsId.name: tLiMacFilterParamsId
tLiMacFilterParamsId.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsId indicates the secondary index for this entry. Every LI MAC filter may have multiple match entries, therefore every LI MAC filter match entry is identified by the tLiFilterName and tLiMacFilterParamsId.

tLiMacFilterParamsRowStatus.name: tLiMacFilterParamsRowStatus
tLiMacFilterParamsRowStatus.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tLiMacFilterParamsLastChanged.name: tLiMacFilterParamsLastChanged
tLiMacFilterParamsLastChanged.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this entry. If no changes were made to the entry since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tLiMacFilterParamsDescription.name: tLiMacFilterParamsDescription
tLiMacFilterParamsDescription.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsDescription specifies a description for this entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsFrameType.name: tLiMacFilterParamsFrameType
tLiMacFilterParamsFrameType.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsFrameType specifies the type of mac frame for which we are defining this match criterium.

tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC.name: tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC
tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC specifies the source MAC address to match for this LI MAC filter entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask.name: tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask
tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMACMask specifies the source MAC mask value for this LI MAC filter match entry. The mask is ANDed with the MAC to match tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC. A zero bit means ignore this bit, do not match. A one bit means match this bit with tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC. Use the value 00-00-00-00-00-00 to disable this filter criterium. If set to all zero, the value of tLiMacFilterParamsSrcMAC will bet set to all zero by the system, and any attept to change this value will be ignored.

tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC.name: tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC
tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC specifies the destination MAC to match for this LI MAC filter entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsDstMACMask.name: tLiMacFilterParamsDstMACMask
tLiMacFilterParamsDstMACMask.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsDstMACMask specifies the destination MAC mask value for this LI MAC filter match entry. The mask is ANDed with the MAC to match tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC. A zero bit means ignore this bit, do not match. a one bit means match this bit with tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC. Use the value 00-00-00-00-00-00 to disable this filter criteria. If set to all zero, the value of tLiMacFilterParamsDstMAC will bet set to all zero by the system, and any attept to change this value will be ignored.

tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitCount.name: tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitCount
tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitCount.description: The object tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitCount indicates the number of times an ingress packet matched this entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitCount.name: tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitCount
tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitCount.description: This object tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitCount indicates the number of times an egress packet matched this entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitBytes.name: tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitBytes
tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitBytes.description: The value of tLiMacFilterParamsIngrHitBytes indicates the number of bytes of all ingress packets that matched this entry.

tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitBytes.name: tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitBytes
tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitBytes.description: The value of tLiMacFilterParamsEgrHitBytes indicates the number of bytes of all egress packets that matched this entry.

tFilterPrefixListTableLstChng.name: tFilterPrefixListTableLstChng
tFilterPrefixListTableLstChng.description: The object tFilterPrefixListTableLstChng indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tFilterPrefixListTable. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, this object contains the value zero.

tFilterPrefixListTable.name: tFilterPrefixListTable
tFilterPrefixListTable.description: The table tFilterPrefixListTable contains an entry for each prefix list defined in the filter area.

tFilterPrefixListType.name: tFilterPrefixListType
tFilterPrefixListType.description: The object TFltrPrefixListType specifies the type of prefix list for the prefix list tFilterPrefixListName.

tFilterPrefixListName.name: tFilterPrefixListName
tFilterPrefixListName.description: The object tFilterPrefixListName specifies the name given to this prefix list.

tFilterPrefixListRowStatus.name: tFilterPrefixListRowStatus
tFilterPrefixListRowStatus.description: The object tFilterPrefixListRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tFilterPrefixListLastChanged.name: tFilterPrefixListLastChanged
tFilterPrefixListLastChanged.description: The object tFilterPrefixListLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of this row. If no changes were made to the row since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains the value zero.

tFilterPrefixListDescription.name: tFilterPrefixListDescription
tFilterPrefixListDescription.description: The object tFilterPrefixListDescription specifies a description for this row.

tFilterPrefixListEntryTblLstChg.name: tFilterPrefixListEntryTblLstChg
tFilterPrefixListEntryTblLstChg.description: The object tFilterPrefixListEntryTblLstChg indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tFilterPrefixListEntryTable. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, this object contains the value zero.

tFilterPrefixListEntryTable.name: tFilterPrefixListEntryTable
tFilterPrefixListEntryTable.description: The table tFilterPrefixListEntryTable contains an entry for each prefix defined in any prefix list defined in the filter area.

tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixType.name: tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixType
tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixType.description: The object tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixType specifies whether the prefix specified in tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefix is an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix. The value of tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixType must match the value of the object tFilterPrefixListType.

tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefix.name: tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefix
tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefix.description: The value of tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefix specifies the IP prefix of this prefix list entry.

tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixLen.name: tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixLen
tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixLen.description: The value of tFilterPrefixListEntryPrefixLen specifiesd the IP prefix length of this prefix list entry.

tFilterPrefixListEntryRowStatus.name: tFilterPrefixListEntryRowStatus
tFilterPrefixListEntryRowStatus.description: The object tFilterPrefixListEntryRowStatus specifies the status of this row.

tFilterPBRDropReason.name: tFilterPBRDropReason
tFilterPBRDropReason.description: Used by tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop to report the failure reason code.

tFilterParmRow.name: tFilterParmRow
tFilterParmRow.description: The value of the object tFilterParmRow indicates the OID of the row status of the applicable filter parameter table. This can be a row from either one of the following tables: - tIPFilterParamsTable; - tMacFilterParamsTable; or - tIPv6FilterParamsTable

tFilterAlarmDescription.name: tFilterAlarmDescription
tFilterAlarmDescription.description: The value of the object tFilterAlarmDescription is a printable character string which contains information about the cause of the problem.

tFilterId.name: tFilterId
tFilterId.description: The value of the object tFilterId, together with the object tFilterType uniquely defines the filter for which this notification is generated.

tFilterType.name: tFilterType
tFilterType.description: The value of the object tFilterType, together with the object tFilterId uniquely defines the filter for which this notification is generated.

tFilterSubInsSpaceOwner.name: tFilterSubInsSpaceOwner
tFilterSubInsSpaceOwner.description: The value of the object tFilterSubInsSpaceOwner, specifies for which application, capable of inserting filter entries, this notification is generated.

tFilterThresholdReached.name: tFilterThresholdReached
tFilterThresholdReached.description: The value of the object tFilterThresholdReached, specifies the threshold reached at the moment this notificastion was generated.

tFltrFlowSpecProblem.name: tFltrFlowSpecProblem
tFltrFlowSpecProblem.description: The value of the object tFltrFlowSpecProblem, indicates which problem has occured while processing a BGP flowspec NLRI in the filter module.

tFltrFlowSpecProblemDescription.name: tFltrFlowSpecProblemDescription
tFltrFlowSpecProblemDescription.description: The value of the object tFltrFlowSpecProblem may contain a more detailed problem description then as given by tFltrFlowSpecProblem.

tFltrFLowSpecNLRI.name: tFltrFLowSpecNLRI
tFltrFLowSpecNLRI.description: The value of the object tFltrFLowSpecNLRI contains at most the first 30 octets of the NLRI causing the problem.

tFltrFlowSpecVrtrId.name: tFltrFlowSpecVrtrId
tFltrFlowSpecVrtrId.description: The value of the object tFltrFlowSpecVrtrId indicates the virtual router Id to which the NLRI belongs.

tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop.name: tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop
tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop.description: The tIPFilterPBRPacketsDrop event is generated either when the configuration of a forwarding action refers to an invalid/unconfigured next-hop or if the active interface goes down operationally in the process of active filtering.

tFilterEntryActivationFailed.name: tFilterEntryActivationFailed
tFilterEntryActivationFailed.description: The tFilterEntryActivationFailed event can only be generated for entries that are controlled by a tmnxTimeRangeEntry. If the tmnxTimeRangeEntry becomes active the indicated entry must be installed. The event is generated when this installation failed because of resource problems.

tFilterEntryActivationRestored.name: tFilterEntryActivationRestored
tFilterEntryActivationRestored.description: The tFilterEntryActivationRestored event can only be generated for entries that are controlled by a tmnxTimeRangeEntry. If the tmnxTimeRangeEntry becomes active the indicated entry must be installed. The event tFilterEntryActivationFailed is generated when this installation originally failed because of resources problems, The notification tFilterEntryActivationRestored is sent when either the time range associated with the filter is no longer active, or when the filter entry was installed due to the availability of new resources.

tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmRaised.name: tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmRaised
tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmRaised.description: The tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmRaised notification is generated when the utilization of a filter entry range that was reserved for filter entry insertion increases to the configured high watermark for his filter

tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmCleared.name: tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmCleared
tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmCleared.description: The tFilterSubInsSpaceAlarmCleared notification is generated when the utilization of a filter entry range that was reserved for filter entry insertion dropped below to the configured low watermark for his filter.

tFilterSubInsFltrEntryDropped.name: tFilterSubInsFltrEntryDropped
